[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**An affordable, AI-powered device for the early detection of oral cancer.**

OroLight is a portable diagnostic tool designed to analyze mouth ulcers and assess their potential to progress into cancerous stages. By combining hardware, computer vision, and machine learning, we aim to make early detection accessible and reliable, especially in low-resource settings.

